				 Trough sets off rain alert
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								The Met office on Sunday warned of widespread rain in Calcutta and the rest of south Bengal in the next 24 hours. Heavy rainfall may occur in isolated places.																								The rainfall will result from a low-pressure trough that has formed over the north-east Bay of Bengal, near the coast of Bangladesh, said G.C. Debnath, the director of the weather section at Regional Meteorological Centre, Alipore.																								In the coastal areas, the rain may be accompanied by gusty winds that may blow at a speed of 45 km per hour.																								The low-pressure trough may intensify. We are watching it closely, said an official.
